description: An anti-terrorism court in Bengaluru convicted Jahidul Islam, the JMB India head, for training youths in Bengal and Assam for jehad. He was sentenced to seven years in prison and fined Rs 57,000. Jahidul, involved in blasts in Burdwan and Bodhgaya, committed dacoities to fund terrorist activities, and NIA seized explosive materials during raids.
title: JMB's India head gets 7-yr RI for training gullible youths
Dispute over funeral rites triggers clash in Bastar; 8 injured, 5 held

description: Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee announced the renaming of Kolkata's Star Theatre to Binodini Theatre to honor actress Binodini Dasi, who was marginalized due to her origins. The current Star Theatre, built in 1887, will reflect this change. This move addresses a historical injustice and celebrates Binodini's significant contributions to Bengali theatre.
title: Didi corrects a historical wrong, renames theatre after 19th century actor

description: Three minor girls from Maharashtra faked their abduction to travel to South Korea and meet K-pop band BTS. They were intercepted by police en route to Pune and counselled about the ill effects of excessive social media exposure. Their families were also advised to limit their screen time. No offence was registered.
title: 3 Maha girls stage own abduction in bid to meet K-Pop band BTS

description: During her Sandeshkhali rally, Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee warned women against trusting miscreants and reiterated that they need not depend on anyone to access governmental schemes. She emphasized self-respect over money, announced 63 projects worth Rs 123 crore for Sandeshkhali, and assured efficient delivery of state benefits.
title: 'Lies don't stick for long': Mamata in Sandeshkhali

description: Shatrughan Shah, a vegetable vendor, lost his auto rickshaw and suffered burn injuries in a fire on Jaipur-Ajmer highway due to an LPG tanker collision. Despite his injuries, his name was left off the official injured list, leaving him without compensation. Shah hopes the authorities will still help him.
title: Auto owner who helped save lives in Jaipur tanker blaze fights for survival
Forces flush out gunmen, destroy 4 bunkers, occupy 3 in Manipur

description: An eight-minute audio clip featuring a heated conversation between Goldy Brar, a Lawrence Bishnoi gang member, and DSP Bikram Singh Brar of Punjab's AGTF has surfaced. Goldy, wanted for the murder of Sidhu Moose Wala, threatened the DSP for employing informers. Bikram, known for his gallantry, dismissed Goldy's threats, asserting adherence to the law.
title: Viral audio clip shows 'Goldy Brar' warning DSP over use of 'informers'

description: Chinese hackers breached the US Treasury by exploiting a third-party software service, accessing unclassified documents and workstations. The investigation, led by the FBI and other agencies, links the attack to state-sponsored activities by China. The Treasury is enhancing its cybersecurity measures and collaborating with partners to safeguard their systems.
title: Chinese hackers breach US Treasury; Third-party alert triggers probe

description: A petition has been filed at Indore High Court to halt the transportation of Union Carbide waste to Pithampur, citing potential health risks. The petitioners call for a judicial committee to assess the impact and have raised concerns about the lack of public consultation and potential hazards to local residents and the environment.
title: Docs move HC to pause transfer of Bhopal gas tragedy waste

description: The framing of charges in the SSC cash-for-jobs case in West Bengal was postponed as accused Sujay Krishna Bhadra fell ill and was hospitalized. Accused individuals, including ex-minister Partha Chatterjee, face money laundering charges. The proceedings will resume on January 2 once all accused are present.
title: Accused in West Bengal jobs scam falls ill, framing of charges stalled

description: Centre has assigned senior IPS officer Vitul Kumar to officiate as Director General of CRPF following the retirement of Anish Dayal Singh on Dec 31. Kumar, currently Special DG of CRPF, will serve until a regular appointment is made. Kumar's career highlights include multiple promotions, accolades, and leadership roles within the police force.
title: UP cadre IPS Vitul Kumar appointed as DG of CRPF
Telgi scam: Five get 3-year jail, fined Rs 50,000 each

description: A local court in Ahmedabad acquitted five individuals charged with cow slaughter and attempting to sell beef due to insufficient evidence. Critical meat samples were not sent for forensic analysis, as required by the Gujarat Animal Preservation Rule. The court also noted the absence of the FSL officer who failed to testify, despite multiple summons.
title: 5 acquitted as cops fail to send 'beef' samples to lab, witnesses turn hostile

description: Karnataka's Congress government has assigned the CID to investigate the suicide of contractor Sachin Panchala, who left a note alleging threats from an aide of minister Priyank Kharge. With the BJP demanding a CBI probe and Priyank's resignation, state home minister Parameshwara defended the CID's capability to handle the investigation.
title: K’taka govt orders CID probe into suicide case with Kharge son ‘link’

description: Construction of the Ram temple in Ayodhya is progressing rapidly and is expected to be completed by June 2025. Important features include 85 murals, titanium lattices, and marble idols. Additional structures like ramparts and shoe racks are set to be finished by September 2025.
title: June deadline for Ram temple complex: Panel

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh reviewed the Army War College's quantum technology and AI labs, citing their role in adaptive warfare. He highlighted India's significant growth in defence exports and articulated the nation's goal to be an economic and military powerhouse by 2047 through strong security and economic integration.
title: Mastering frontier techs need of hour, Defence minister Rajnath tells forces
SP team meets Sambhal unrest victims' families, gives them Rs 5 lakh

description: Launched in 2022, the Tele-Manas helpline has catered to 16.6 lakh calls, operating 24x7 across India with 53 operational cells. The system is structured in two tiers, involving state cells and specialist resources, and now includes video consultations in selected regions.
title: Govt's mental health line gets 16.6 lakh calls since 2022 launch

description: The Indian government is vigilantly monitoring the situation of Indian H-1B visa holders in the US amid backlash and profiling of IT and management professionals. This involves collaboration between the ministries of external affairs, commerce, and IT to ensure that legal Indian workers are not adversely impacted by evolving American visa policies under Donald Trump's administration.
title: Govt on alert over H-1B row, taking feedback from IT firms

description: Elon Musk moderated his support for H-1B visas, admitting the program needs reform due to backlash from MAGA hardliners. Musk suggested raising the minimum salary to fix the system, which critics claim favors lower-wage IT workers. MAGA supporters argue that the program undermines American jobs and favors foreign workers.
title: Musk v MAGA: Faced with nativist fury, Elon dials down support for H-1B, calls for reform

description: Andhra Pradesh deputy CM Pawan Kalyan praised Telangana CM Revanth Reddy and criticized Allu Arjun's team for their handling of the 'Pushpa 2' stampede. A 35-year-old woman died, and her son was injured. Pawan Kalyan emphasized the film industry should have supported the victim's family and not blamed Arjun solely.
title: Allu Arjun's uncle Pawan Kalyan blames Team Pushpa for stampede

description: Protests intensify across Bihar demanding cancellation of BPSC prelims, alleging corruption. Demonstrators halt trains and block roads, with political parties and student groups joining in. Chief secretary meets aspirants, but no official statement yet from CM. Police action criticized by political leaders; support offered by various political figures. Protests continue with threats of indefinite hunger strike.
title: Bihar exam stir intensifies as protesters block trains, roads

description: A Santacruz businessman has been sentenced to 20 years of rigorous imprisonment for attempting to smuggle 4,365kg of hashish in drums of mango chutney, 37 years after the drugs were found. Despite health issues, the court found no mitigating circumstances, emphasizing the gravity of drug trafficking. Bhanushali, with prior convictions, showed no remorse.
title: 4,300kg hash hidden in drums 37 yrs ago gets man 20 yrs’ RI
J&K drops Sheikh Abdullah anniv from holiday list

description: The government requires additional time to allocate land for former PM Manmohan Singh’s memorial as a trust needs to be formed first. Preliminary assessments are being conducted for available land near Rajghat, and a trust application is necessary for the process to proceed. The memorial will follow procedures similar to those for Atal Bihari Vajpayee’s memorial.
title: No trust, land grant for Manmohan Singh's memorial some days away

description: The Washington Wizards will face the New York Knicks at Capital One Arena on December 30, 2024. The Knicks, on a seven-game winning streak, recently defeated the Wizards. Key players to watch include Jalen Brunson and Karl-Anthony Towns for the Knicks, and Jordan Poole and Kyle Kuzma for the Wizards. Tune in at 7:00 PM ET.
title: Knicks vs Wizards (12/30): Lineups, injuries, prediction, betting tips, how to watch

description: The Centre has declared the Wayanad landslides in Kerala, which occurred on July 30, as a disaster of severe nature. The catastrophic event claimed over 200 lives, injured many, and caused significant displacement. The Union home ministry has assured additional assistance through the National Disaster Response Fund.
title: 5 months on, Centre declares Wayanad landslides 'severe' nature disaster
Iraqi couple charged for abusing Yazidi girls as slaves in Germany

description: Congress criticises PM Modi for his silence on the rupee's depreciation against the US dollar, contrasting it with his previous attacks on former PM Manmohan Singh over similar issues. The rupee has reached an all-time low of 85.27 per USD. Questions arise about the RBI's currency stabilization efforts despite significant interventions.
title: Cong slams BJP over depreciating rupee, reminds PM Modi of 2013 remarks

description: A recent study has shown that smoking a single cigarette cuts 17 minutes off a man's life and 22 minutes off a woman’s. Smokers lose 10-11 years of life expectancy on average compared to non-smokers. Researchers stress the critical importance of quitting, as smoking causes significant harm throughout life and the healthiest option is complete cessation.
title: Smoking takes much larger toll on life expectancy, reveals study

description: Parents were outraged after discovering that Wulidianzi School in Liaoning province served students food stored in containers previously used for dog food. Younger students ate leftovers collected from older students, leading to illness. Local authorities are investigating. The incident sparked heavy criticism on social media, calling for strict punishment and better surveillance to prevent such incidents in the future.

description: Donald Trump won the 2024 presidential election, overcoming legal challenges, an assassination attempt, and a divided Republican Party. His victory, despite various controversies and a struggling Democratic campaign led by Kamala Harris, marked a significant political resurgence and prompted global speculation about his second term.
title: Comeback that shocked US: The 12 months that led to Trump's re-election

description: Gen Z's slang in 2024 saw terms like 'brain rot,' 'demure,' and 'manifest' become increasingly popular. Dictionaries highlighted these words, reflecting digital media's impact, societal trends, and polarisation. Notable mentions include 'brat,' 'rawdogging,' and 'kakistocracy,' capturing cultural shifts and anxieties, while 'lavender marriage' emerged as a unique relationship concept.

description: India neared joining nations with space-docking technology as Isro launched the SpaDeX mission, putting two satellites in space for docking attempts. The mission, crucial for Chandrayaan-4 and Bhartiya Antriksh Station, also included astrobiology experiments and payloads from private sector startups and educational institutions onboard POEM.

description: The verdict relied on testimonies from more than 70 witnesses, forensic evidence and CCTV footage capturing the crime.
title: Chennai stalker who pushed student in front of moving train sentenced to death

description: The 49ers host the Lions in a Week 17 Monday Night Football game. San Francisco is out of playoff contention, while Detroit seeks the top seed. The Lions miss star running back David Montgomery, out for the season due to a torn MCL.
title: Will David Montgomery play against the San Francisco 49ers tonight?

description: Generation Beta, starting from 2025, will consist of individuals born up to 2039. This cohort will see AI and automation seamlessly integrated into daily life, influencing education, work, and healthcare. Shaped by Millennials and older Gen Z parents, Beta babies will prioritize sustainability and individuality while balancing digital interactions with personal expression.
title: Move over Gen Z and Gen Alpha, new Generation Beta to start from 2025

description: A controversy arose in Pune after a pub sent guests condoms and oral rehydration sachets as part of their New Year's Eve party invitation, sparking backlash from the Maharashtra Pradesh Youth Congress. The Congress has demanded strict action against the pub's management, citing an unsuitable marketing strategy. Police have begun recording statements from attendees.

description: In 2024, around the world, various protests and social movements highlighted demands for justice and rights. Major events included Bangladesh's governmental resignation, Russian anti-Putin protests, Afghan women's dissent against regressive laws, university pro-Palestinian demonstrations, and resistance against LGBTQ+ discrimination.

description: The Civil Aviation Ministry clarified that Digi Yatra does not share passenger data with tax authorities. The system erases data within 24 hours of a flight’s departure, and the app stores information solely on the user’s device. Digi Yatra is currently for domestic use only and not available for international flights.
title: Is Digi Yatra data shared with tax authorities? Centre clarifies

description: Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, who retired from T20 internationals six months ago, are now struggling in Test cricket. Rohit has had a poor year with low scores and questions about his captaincy, while Virat faces technical challenges and lack of confidence. India's Test cricket transition faces a critical moment.
title: Poor returns in 2024 add to Rohit Sharma, Kohli's woes in Test cricket

description: Arshad Khan, a businessman from Govandi, has been arrested for allegedly receiving ₹46 lakh from Ego Media Private Limited, linked to a hoarding collapse that killed 17 people. The crime branch discovered financial transfers totaling one crore from Ego Media's directors. Police have arrested four individuals, including Ego Media's directors.

description: The Tamil Nadu police had sent a letter to the NIC requesting the blocking of FIR views for sensitive cases, particularly those involving crimes against women and children.

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal showcased determination and composure during India's chase of 340 against Australia. Despite the top order's struggle, his 84 runs and an 88-run partnership with Rishabh Pant kept India hopeful. However, Pant's dismissal led to a collapse, and Australia won by 184 runs as India got all out for 155.

description: NCW chief Vijaya Rahatkar revealed that the accused in the Anna University assault case is a habitual offender. A two-member NCW committee is investigating. The Madras High Court has ordered a special investigation team and Rs 25 lakh compensation for the survivor due to FIR leakage, to be recovered from the responsible police personnel's salaries.
title: Anna univ assault case: NCW panel flags 'shortcomings' in police, admin

description: Apple is seeking to reduce its reliance on Nvidia by renting GPU access from cloud providers and collaborating with Broadcom to develop its own AI server chip, targeting mass production by 2026. This move aims to achieve technological autonomy and is driven by both financial motives and longstanding corporate disputes.
title: What is behind Apple's 'allergy' to the world's biggest AI chip company Nvidia

description: Indian captain Rohit Sharma clarified that Shubman Gill was not dropped for the Boxing Day Test, but selected an all-rounder Washington Sundar to strengthen the lower middle-order batting. Sunil Gavaskar criticized the decision, emphasizing that it effectively sidelined Gill. Sundar contributed with 19 overs and a 50-run knock, but India still faced defeat, trailing 1-2 in the series.

description: In 2024, India faced intense diplomatic challenges amidst regional tensions and international incidents. From strained relations with Canada and Bangladesh to resolving the border dispute with China, India's diplomatic efforts were rigorously tested. It achieved significant wins including securing the release of Indian naval personnel from Qatar and signing new agreements with Sri Lanka and Iran.

description: Andhra Pradesh CM N Chandrababu Naidu is the wealthiest with assets over Rs 931 crore, while West Bengal's CM Mamata Banerjee is the least wealthy at Rs 15 lakh. The per capita net national income is Rs 1,85,854, and average CM income stands 7.3 times higher.

description: Andhra Pradesh deputy Chief Minister Pawan Kalyan addressed the stampede incident at Sandhya Theater and criticized the delayed response to the victim's family. He defended actor Allu Arjun, emphasising the collective responsibility of the film industry.

description: Sangeeta Bijlani hints at Salman Khan while discussing past control over her clothing. Malaika Arora reflects on personal growth post-breakup with Arjun Kapoor. Anushka Sharma and Athiya Shetty's reactions at India vs Australia Test go viral. Shweta Tiwari addresses Palak-Ibrahim relationship rumors. Bachchans attend a wedding, dismissing divorce speculation.

description: In September, Australian athlete Lily Winward, 19, was forced to travel with a toddler on her lap due to an Etihad Airways overbooking issue during a layover in the UAE. Despite paying $3,000 for her flights, Winward's attempts to address the situation have so far been ignored by the airline.

description: Former cricketer Irfan Pathan raises concerns about Rohit Sharma's place in India's Test team due to his poor form, suggesting his captaincy is keeping him in the playing XI. Pathan points out better-performing options like KL Rahul are being overlooked. Rohit’s struggles have coincided with India's lackluster performances in the ongoing series against Australia.

description: Australia captain Pat Cummins praises India's Jasprit Bumrah as the most influential player in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy series. Cummins acknowledges Bumrah's challenging performance, particularly highlighting his 9/156 figures in the Melbourne Test. Despite India's fight, Australia secured an 184-run victory with Cummins named 'Player of the Match.'

description: In 2024, Google’s Year in Search revealed the most popular TV shows and movies capturing global interest. Shows like 'Baby Reindeer' and 'Fallout' topped the list, while movies such as 'Inside Out 2' and 'Deadpool & Wolverine' also gained significant traction.
title: 10 shows on OTT platforms that world searched most in 2024

description: Chirag Paswan, an NDA ally, criticized lathicharge and water cannons used on students protesting in Patna over alleged BPSC exam irregularities. He urged Bihar's chief minister Nitish Kumar for immediate intervention. Paswan called for dialogue to address the students' concerns peacefully and emphasized swift government action to restore trust while avoiding political influence.
title: BPSC row: NDA ally Chirag Paswan slams Nitish govt over lathicharge

description: Pollsters faced significant challenges and inaccuracies during the 2024 elections in India and the United States. Despite predictions for the BJP and NDA, actual outcomes were unexpected. Key states like Odisha, Andhra Pradesh, Haryana, Maharashtra, Jharkhand, and swing states in the US contradicted exit polls, highlighting the limitations and pressures faced by psephologists.

description: India's Jasprit Bumrah is nominated for ICC Men's Cricketer of the Year and Test Cricketer of the Year for his exceptional 2024 performance. Competitors include England's Joe Root and Harry Brook, Australia's Travis Head, and Sri Lanka's Kamindu Mendis. Bumrah's consistent performance across conditions stands out.

description: Former England spinner Monty Panesar believes India's head coach is frustrated with Shubman Gill's inability to convert promising starts into big innings. Despite Gill's potential, his Test average of 35.76 is seen as below expectations. Gill's recent performances and his dropping from the Melbourne Test are seen as a wake-up call for him to improve.

description: Google is ramping up its AI strategy for 2025, with DeepMind co-founder Demis Hassabis promising significant product advancements to counter ChatGPT's dominance. CEO Sundar Pichai emphasized the importance of 2025 in a company-wide meeting, highlighting the launch of Project Astra and updates to Gemini. Despite entering the AI race later, Pichai remains confident in Google's potential to lead.

description: Ladakh councillor Konchok Stanzin criticized the Indian Army's installation of Chhatrapati Shivaji's statue by Pangong lake, expressing concerns about its relevance to the local environment. Highlighting the lack of local input, he called for projects that better reflect the community. The statue's unveiling follows the India-China border disengagement, amid ongoing protests for greater autonomy in Ladakh.

description: Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena expressed his objections to Delhi CM Atishi over Arvind Kejriwal referring to her as a 'temporary CM'. Saxena emphasized the insult to her and criticized Kejriwal's statements as unconstitutional. He praised Atishi's governance approach and articulated challenges left by the previous administration, while condemning unfounded allegations against her and the negative political discourse.

description: BJP’s Amit Malviya countered AAP MP Sanjay Singh's claim that the BJP tried to remove his wife's name from the Delhi voter list, asserting her vote in Delhi was invalid as she is registered in UP's Sultanpur. Sanjay Singh alleged BJP was deleting Purvanchali voters' names in Delhi, and announced plans for a defamation case.

description: Two individuals were arrested for attacking a senior officer at an NCC camp in Kerala after 86 cadets fell ill from suspected food poisoning. Investigations revealed unhygienic kitchen conditions and two workers without health cards. The camp was paused and will resume after safety measures are ensured. Probes have been launched to investigate the incident.

description: Rahul Gandhi criticizes BJP for the death of a Dalit youth in police custody in Madhya Pradesh and the abuse of tribal women in Odisha, attributing such acts to BJP's 'Manuvadi thinking'. Both incidents have sparked protests and condemnations, highlighting ongoing caste-based atrocities.

description: Samajwadi Party visited Sambhal district, giving Rs 5 lakh each to families of those killed in the recent mosque survey violence. The delegation questioned the justice system and highlighted injustice while 50 individuals have been arrested so far, including a significant arrest made in Delhi.
title: SP delegation visits Sambhal, gives Rs 5 lakh to kin of victims

description: Magnus Carlsen confirmed his return to the World Blitz Chess Championship after FIDE permitted players to compete in jeans. Carlsen criticized FIDE's decision-making process and deputy president Viswanathan Anand, claiming the situation was mishandled and Anand was not suitable for his role. Carlsen faced fines and rules clarification issues.

description: A Jeju Air Boeing 737-800 returned to Seoul's Gimpo International Airport due to landing gear issues, following a similar model's fatal crash the previous day. The flight was heading to Jeju island but landed back safely. South Korea plans comprehensive inspections of all Boeing 737-800 aircraft, with American investigators possibly joining the crash probe.

description: The BJP criticized AAP's promise to give a monthly honorarium to temple pujaris and gurdwara granthis, accusing AAP of remembering religious figures only during elections. BJP questioned AAP's past funding decisions and urged transparency in the registration and funding of the new scheme.
title: 'Remember Ram only when ...': BJP's jab at AAP's scheme for priests

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal showcased exceptional form in the 2024 Boxing Day Test against Australia, scoring crucial half-centuries in both innings. Despite his efforts, India lost by 184 runs. Jaiswal ended the year as the second-highest run-scorer in Test cricket with 1478 runs, narrowly missing Sachin Tendulkar's record for most Test runs in a calendar year by an Indian.

description: Rishabh Pant faced backlash for his reckless shot selection during India's run-chase in the Boxing Day Test against Australia, contributing to a batting collapse. description: H-1B visa row: Perplexity AI founder Aravind Srinivas points out that the US dispute over Indian immigrants and H-1B visas lacks factual basis. He suggests that unauthorized immigration is the real issue.

He notes that peak migration aligns with rapid national development, as seen in other Asian economies. Vembu also stresses the importance of building domestic capabilities amid ongoing discussions on talent retention.

title: Allu Arjun stampede case: Decision on counter police affidavit pushed to Jan 3

title: 4th Test: India 'collapse' to 184-run defeat as Australia take 2-1 series lead

description: A Jeju Air flight from Bangkok to South Korea crashed during landing, killing 179 of the 181 onboard. The crash involved a 15-year-old Boeing 737-800 and may have been caused by a bird strike and landing gear malfunction. Both black boxes were recovered to assist with the investigation.
title: Pilot declared 'Mayday': Key points in South Korea plane crash

description: India skipper Rohit Sharma highlighted the heavy workload and lack of support for Jasprit Bumrah after their defeat in the fourth Test in Melbourne. Bumrah's exceptional bowling performance was insufficient to secure a win, raising concerns over his physical toll. Rohit called for better team support ahead of the crucial final Test in Sydney.
title: 'Risk of over-bowling Bumrah': Rohit Sharma after MCG defeat

description: India's well-known batting lineup faltered again in the Border Gavaskar Trophy, resulting in a 284-run defeat to Australia, giving them a 2-1 series lead. Except for Yashasvi Jaiswal's 84, the other batsmen failed to secure a draw. India needs a win in Sydney to retain the trophy as the defending champions.
title: Explained: How India can retain BGT despite Melbourne defeat

description: In December 2024, a rare celestial event known as the Black Moon will occur, marking the second new moon in a single month. This phenomenon, happening on December 30, 2024, will not be visible but will create ideal conditions for stargazing. Astronomers and enthusiasts can observe distant celestial bodies like galaxies, nebulae, and planets.
title: Black Moon 2024: Stargazing time & significance of rare celestial event

description: Beware of fraudulent emails claiming to be from the Income Tax Department about downloading e-PAN cards. These emails are part of a phishing scam exploiting interest in the PAN 2.0 initiative.
title: Beware of e-PAN card scam! Got email to download PAN? Check this

description: Bengaluru police arrested four individuals, including an Axis Bank relationship manager, for defrauding Cred of Rs 12 crore. The group used fake documents and manipulated bank details to withdraw the funds. The scam was uncovered after detecting suspicious transactions in Dreamplug Paytech Solutions' accounts.
title: 14 days, 37 transactions ...: Cred lost Rs 12 cr in fraud from Axis Bank accounts

description: India captain Rohit Sharma defended the third umpire's decision in the 'controversial' dismissal of Yashasvi Jaiswal during the fourth Border-Gavaskar Test. Despite Snicko not showing a spike, visual evidence suggested a clear deflection. Jaiswal's exit led to India's batting collapse, ultimately falling 184 runs short of the target, impacting their World Test Championship qualification hopes.
title: Rohit Sharma on Yashasvi's dismissal: 'It looked like he touched it'

description: AAP has announced a monthly honorarium of Rs 18,000 for temple pujaris and Gurudwara granthis if re-elected in the upcoming Delhi assembly polls. Registration starts at Hanuman temple in Connaught Place. Kejriwal assured there will be no fund shortage for this scheme aimed at supporting religious workers.
title: AAP to provide Rs 18k monthly to temple 'priests', gurdwara 'granthis'

description: The Congress party clarifies the absence of top leaders during the immersion of former PM Manmohan Singh's ashes, emphasizing respect for family privacy. The BJP criticizes the Gandhi family's absence. Singh's ashes were immersed in the Yamuna River by his family following Sikh rituals.
title: Cong shares why Gandhis didn’t join Manmohan Singh’s kin for ash immersion

description: Rohit Sharma's underwhelming performance in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, scoring only 31 runs in five innings, coupled with unsuccessful captaincy decisions, may prompt his retirement post-series. The Indian selectors are already aware, focusing now on the transition to the next generation of players.
title: Shouldn't Rohit Sharma retire right away and not after SCG?

description: In a dramatic moment during the fifth day of the fourth Test at Melbourne, Pat Cummins successfully reviewed a caught behind decision, getting Yashasvi Jaiswal out for 84 runs. Despite Snickometer showing no spike, the third umpire relied on visual evidence to overturn the on-field decision.  Yashasvi’s outstanding performances this year have cemented his place among India’s cricketing greats. He has amassed 1,478 Test runs in 2024, placing him third on India’s list of most runs in a calendar year.
title: Snickometer fails, 'visual evidence' rules Yashasvi Jaiswal out

description: Jasprit Bumrah achieved another milestone with a nine-wicket match haul at the MCG, making him the first pacer in 16 years to surpass 70 wickets in a year. His exceptional performance includes three fifers in the current series against Australia, showcasing his dominance as a lone warrior in India's bowling line-up despite limited support.
title: IND vs AUS: Dial Jasprit Bumrah for everything!

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal confronted on-field umpires after the third umpire controversially declared him out on a doubtful caught-behind appeal during the crucial final day of the Boxing Day Test against Australia. Jaiswal's dismissal left India in a difficult position, chasing 340 runs with a score of 140 for 7.
title: Who's the third umpire who gave Yashasvi Jaiswal out

description: Radhika Gupta, CEO of Edelweiss Mutual Funds, shares her experience on Shark Tank India Season 3. She explains her tough demeanor on the show is influenced by her male-dominated finance profession and personal insecurities. Despite early career challenges, her expertise eventually earned clients' trust.
title: Shark Radhika Gupta gets candid about her journey with Shark Tank India

description: Rishabh Pant faced criticism for his batting in the first innings of the Melbourne Test, but looked to have corrected that in the second. But after a strong 88-run partnership with Yashasvi Jaiswal, Pant got out while playing an unncessary big shot against part-time spinner Travis Head. This triggered a mini-collapse, with India slipping from 121 for 3 to 130 for 6, while chasing a target of 340.
title: Watch: Pant's rush of blood costs India dear in Melbourne

description: Suchir Balaji, a researcher at OpenAI, was found dead in his apartment, and while police ruled it a suicide, his mother disputes this. She demands an FBI investigation, citing signs of a struggle and a private autopsy that contradicts the police's findings. S
title: Suchir Balaji's mother says his death not suicide; Elon Musk 'replies'

description: India were struggling at 59/3, chasing 340 in the fourth Test at Melbourne, when a 'bail switch' incident occurred between Mitchell Starc and Yashasvi Jaiswal. Australia was bowled out for 234, with Jasprit Bumrah claiming his third five-wicket haul of the series.
title: Watch: Starc sledges Jaiswal, Indian opener responds

description: Maulana Shahabuddin Razvi Barelvi, National President of All India Muslim Jamaat, issued a fatwa against New Year celebrations, urging Muslims to focus on religious observances. He advised young Muslims to refrain from partaking in New Year festivities. Razvi opposed lifting the ban on Salman Rushdie's The Satanic Verses, citing potential harm to the social and religious fabric of the country.
title: All India Muslim Jamaat issues fatwa discouraging New Year celebrations

description: Tonight at 10 pm, India will launch its SpaDeX mission using the PSLV-C60 rocket. This mission involves two 220 kg spacecraft performing complex in-space docking maneuvers in a 470 km orbit, crucial for future lunar missions and the Bharatiya Antariksh Station. The mission also includes tests of indigenous technologies and secondary scientific experiments.
title: Isro set to launch PSLV-C60 Spadex Space Docking mission at 10pm today
'Water cannon, lathi charge in harsh cold inhuman': Priyanka on BPSC stir

description: A 21-year-old man in Mandya district died after detonating a gelatin stick in front of the house of the girl he loved, following her family's rejection. The police report that the man had a prior legal history for eloping with the underage girl and faced resistance from her family. His family has lodged a complaint about his death.
title: 'Jilted' Karnataka man blows himself up in front of lover's house

description: Elon Musk supports the H-1B visa system, describing it as broken and needing reform. He suggests raising the minimum salary and adding a yearly cost to make hiring foreign workers more expensive. Trump's recent appointment of Sriram Krishnan as senior AI policy advisor has intensified debates within the MAGA community over immigration policies for skilled workers.
title: Elon Musk says H-1B visa program 'broken', needs major reform

description: West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee plans her first visit to Sandeshkhali after violent protests over local TMC leaders' alleged sexual harassment. The visit aims to promote state welfare programs and rebuild community trust. Several women in the community express anticipation and hope for the chief minister's support.
title: Mamata Banerjee to visit Sandeshkhali today, first time since protests

description: Rohit Sharma's struggles continue despite resuming his opening role in the Boxing Day Test, amassing an average of 6.20 in five innings so far in this Border Gavaskar Trophy. This performance risks him having the lowest average for a visiting captain in Australia. He missed the first Test due to paternity leave, while Jasprit Bumrah captained India to victory.
title: Rohit Sharma 'version 6.20' - worse than Courtney Walsh
'Israeli spies found out about Hezbollah commander’s 4 mistresses, marriage plans'

description: A Jeju Air flight from Bangkok to South Korea crashed at Muan International Airport, killing 179 people. Two flight attendants were the only survivors and are being treated for serious injuries and psychological trauma. The crash occurred due to the failure of the plane's landing gear, causing the jetliner to skid off the runway and catch fire.
title: 'Why am I here?': Survivors of South Korean plane crash left in shock

description: Conor McGregor and Logan Paul are set to compete in a significant boxing match in 2025, with each fighter potentially earning $250 million. The event, organized by the Ambani family and part of India's tourism campaign, will be held at Mumbai's Wankhede Stadium. Jake Paul, Logan's brother, seeks involvement in the negotiations, adding complexity to the arrangements.
title: Paul vs. McGregor: Wankhede stadium gears up for a $250mln fight

description: Conor McGregor plans a return to combat sports with a boxing exhibition against Logan Paul in India, scheduled for 2025. This event, linked to India's tourism campaign, will occur at Mumbai's Wankhede Stadium. McGregor could earn $250 million. However, complications arise due to his ongoing UFC contract requiring approval for non-UFC bouts.
title: Conor McGregor vs Logan Paul in India? UFC star almost 'confirms' it

description: Shariq Satha, a gangster with alleged links to Dawood Ibrahim and Pakistan's ISI, is suspected to have orchestrated the recent violence in Sambhal from Dubai. Investigators found foreign-made cartridges and unusual money transfers indicating his involvement. Previously, bullets from Pakistan and the US were discovered, suggesting a foreign connection.
title: Who is Shariq Satha? Gangster with 'ties' to Dawood behind Sambhal violence

description: A new attendance record for a Test match in Australia has been set at the MCG with over 350,700 attendees across five days of the fourth Test between Australia and India, surpassing the previous record from 1937. The crowds were extraordinary, with daily tallies exceeding expectations. Parking issues on the fifth day caused delays for some fans.
title: IND vs AUS Test breaks all-time attendance record at MCG

description: Jasprit Bumrah became the first visiting bowler to take 30 wickets in a Test series in Australia since Curtly Ambrose's 1992-93 feat. Also, he is only the second Indian to the mark after spin legend Bishan Singh Bedi did that on the 1967-68 tour. His exceptional bowling averages and multiple five-wicket hauls highlight an extraordinary performance in Test cricket history.
title: Bumrah's 'Super-30' in Australia matches Ambrose, Bedi

description: Jimmy Carter, the 39th US President, who passed away at 100, had strong connections with India. His 1978 visit led to a Haryana village being renamed 'Carterpuri'. Carter praised Indian democracy and signed the Delhi Declaration, strengthening Indo-US ties based on shared democratic values.
title: Jimmy Carter's India connection: Village was named 'Carterpuri' in his honour

description: On the final day of the Boxing Day Test, a tense battle unfolded between Yashasvi Jaiswal and Mitchell Starc. Starc's attempts to unsettle Jaiswal with mind games and sledging were met with defiance as Jaiswal maintained his composure. Despite Australia's early breakthroughs, Jaiswal's grit and determination kept India's chase alive, adding to the intense encounter.
title: Watch: Bail switch is back! Jaiswal-Starc antics take center stage

description: Prashant Kishore is facing legal action for joining student protests demanding a re-examination for the BPSC exam in Patna. Despite police warnings and confrontations, Kishore, along with the Jan Suraaj party and several students, pursued the demonstration. Police used water cannons and detained some protesters, leading to injuries and further tensions.
title: FIR against Prashant Kishore for 'organising' BPSC protest without 'permission'

description: Parts of north India, including Punjab, Haryana, Delhi, and Rajasthan, are expected to experience a drop in night temperatures by three to four degrees in the coming days. The IMD has issued warnings about cold waves and dense fog for the year-end and New Year.
title: Cold wave likely in parts of north India from today

description: In Bigg Boss 18, tensions rise as Vivian Dsena confronts Karan Veer Mehra over their friendship. The episode also features a nomination round where contestants nominate each other, including Vivian calling Rajat untrustworthy. Sara Arfeen Khan's recent eviction leaves the top 10 contestants battling for the title, intensifying rivalries and alliances.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Vivian Dsena questions Karan Veer Mehra about his friendship

description: In 2024, the top 10 climate disasters inflicted over $288 billion in damages and claimed over 2,000 lives globally, with the US bearing nearly half the financial burden. South-east Asia accounted for over 40% of the casualties. The report highlights the disproportionate impact on lower-income countries and underscores the urgent need to transition away from fossil fuels.
title: 2,000 dead, $288 billion lost to top 10 climate disasters in 2024: Report
Liam Payne' close friend among 5 charged over One Direction star’s drug death

description: Australia captain Pat Cummins sets a new record in Test cricket by dismissing India's Rohit Sharma six times. Cummins surpasses Richie Benaud's previous record. Cummins' tactical excellence has repeatedly outmaneuvered Rohit, including dismissing him four times in the current series. Other notable captains include Imran Khan and Kapil Dev. The five-match Test series is currently locked at 1-1.
title: Pat Cummins outwits Rohit Sharma in record-breaking battle
Buy or sell: Stocks on brokerages’ radar for December 30

description: Experts caution against relying on chatbots for sensitive information, particularly for health advice. Surveys show increasing use of AI for guidance, but personal, financial, and medical details should not be shared with chatbots due to privacy risks and potential misuse of information.
title: 7 Things you should never-ever tell or ask from ChatGPT and other AI Chatbots

description: Suchir Balaji’s parents dispute the ruling of his death as suicide, alleging foul play and demanding an FBI investigation. Three months prior, Balaji had accused OpenAI of copyright violations, which his parents believe put him at risk. The investigation remains ongoing, with the family seeking justice.
title: Watch: 'Blood shots in bathroom', Suchir Balaji's parents reject suicide ruling

description: Jasprit Bumrah surpasses Shoaib Akhtar's record by achieving his 13th five-wicket haul in Test cricket during the Boxing Day Test against Australia. With 203 wickets in 44 Tests, Bumrah joins an elite group of bowlers, including Michael Holding and Saqlain Mushtaq, who have also accomplished this feat. The series is currently tied 1-1, with the fifth and final match scheduled to take place in Sydney from January 3.
title: Jasprit Bumrah breaks Shoaib Akhtar's record

description: Health insurers in Mumbai paid 71.3% of the Rs 1.2 lakh crore claims outstanding during FY24. Insurers handled over 3 crore claims, with 2.7 crore claims worth Rs 83,493 crore paid. Public sector insurers had the highest incurred claims ratio at 103%. Complaints were notably from Mumbai, Pune, Ahmedabad, and Chandigarh.
title: Health insurers settle 71% of Rs 1.2 lakh crore claims in FY 24

description: The Delhi high court has ruled that contemplating a terrorist act for years, even without executing it, constitutes a punishable offense under UAPA. The court underlined that planning and recruitment efforts, like brainwashing youth for terrorism, fall under terrorist acts, even without executing specific activities.
title: Contemplating terrorist act for years is also an act of terrorism: Delhi HC

description: Elon Musk fiercely defends the H-1B visa program amid a heated debate on immigration reform, clashing with Trump supporter Steven Mackey on X. While Musk credits the program for America's strength in tech, Donald Trump unexpectedly supports Musk's stance, emphasizing his personal use of H-1B visas and its importance in the tech industry.
title: Elon Musk gets support from America’s 'most-important' man on H-1B visa'

description: A baby boy was born in the temporary but well-equipped Central Hospital at the Maha Kumbh Mela site on Sunday, marking an auspicious start to the event. Sonam, a 20-year-old labourer, gave birth to a healthy boy weighing 2.4 kg. Doctors suggested naming the baby Ved.
title: Temporary hospital in Maha Kumbh sees birth of 1st baby

description: The search for missing 22-year-old student Santra Elizabath Saju from Kerala ended in tragedy as a body believed to be hers was found in Almond river, Edinburgh. Santra, a student at Heriot-Watt University, was last seen on Dec 6 in Livingston. Her family has been informed, and police do not suspect foul play.
title: Missing Kerala student found dead in Scotland

description: Calcutta High Court disapproves of trial courts giving unsolicited advice in divorce cases, stating that only the involved couple can judge their ability to reconcile. In a recent case, a trial court had advised a couple to reunite for their son's sake, which the higher court deemed inappropriate.
title: Court 'sermons' on divorce cases draw Calcutta HC ire

description: The road transport ministry has mandated that speed limits and vehicle logos be painted on expressways and National Highways every 10 km to guide drivers. New guidelines also require larger signage at frequent intervals, placement of 'no parking' signage every 5 km, and display of emergency helpline numbers to enhance driving safety.
title: Soon, bigger speed signs at every 10km on NHs, eways

description: Mostly clear skies are expected during the day with maximum temperatures ranging from 12-16 C. A cold wave in the plains is indicated by minimum temperatures of 10 C or less and 4.5 C below normal. A temperature fall is predicted in Uttar Pradesh, Central India, East India, and Maharashtra over the next five days.
title: Central & east India also likely to see dip in temp, says IMD

description: The sale of antidepressants and mood elevators in India increased significantly, growing by 64% to Rs 2,536 crore since 2020, driven by virtual consultations and greater awareness. Key medications like Escitalopram and Clonazepam saw notable increases in sales, reflecting reduced mental health stigma and increased treatment acceptance.
title: Antidepressant sales surge by 64% in India after Covid

description: The government is considering sites near Kisan Ghat and Rashtriya Smriti Sthal for former PM Manmohan Singh's memorial. BJP chief J P Nadda confirmed the allocation of space. While guidelines prefer Rashtriya Smriti Sthal, the final decision will be a political one. The designated spot could accommodate two more memorials despite past constraints.
title: Rashtriya Smriti Sthal, Kisan Ghat on list for Manmohan Singh's memorial
ASI decodes Sanskrit inscription found in POK

description: Union minister Hardeep Puri criticised Congress for creating controversies around the last rites of ex-PM Manmohan Singh, accusing them of disrespecting his memory and ethos. BJP members, including Manjinder Singh Sirsa, participated in the ceremonies, while Congress members were absent. Full state and military honours were accorded to Singh.
title: No one from Gandhi family went to collect MMS remains: Puri

description: The collegium of judges is considering not recommending lawyers or judicial officers with close relatives in the judiciary for HC judge appointments, to eliminate nepotism and give first-generation lawyers more opportunities. Additionally, they have started interacting with candidates to assess their suitability firsthand.
title: In a first, SC collegium starts interacting with lawyers backed for HC judgeship

description: Jasprit Bumrah's impressive five-wicket haul helped India contain Australia to 234 in the final day of the fourth Test at MCG, setting a challenging 340-run target. His dominance at this venue further highlights his exceptional performance in 2024, making him one of Test cricket's premier fast bowlers. With the series locked at 1-1, India secured a commanding 295-run victory in Perth, while Australia responded with a dominant 10-wicket win in Adelaide. ​​​The rain-affected third Test in Brisbane ended in a draw, setting up a thrilling contest in Melbourne.
title: Jasprit Bumrah gives death stare to Nathan Lyon
